<h1 class="page-title">Policy Schema</h1>
<p class="page-desc">JSON IR schema for compiled clash policies. Policies are authored as <a href="/policy/">Starlark (.star) files</a> and compiled to this format.</p>

## Document structure

```json
{
  "schema_version": 4,
  "use": "<policy-name>",
  "default_effect": "<effect>",
  "policies": [
    {
      "name": "<policy-name>",
      "body": [ <rule | include> ]
    }
  ]
}
```

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `schema_version` | integer | Always `4` |
| `use` | string | Name of the entry-point policy |
| `default_effect` | string | Effect when no rule matches: `"allow"`, `"deny"`, or `"ask"` |
| `policies` | array | Named policy blocks |

## Rules

```json
{ "rule": { "effect": "<effect>", "<domain>": <matcher> } }
{ "rule": { "effect": "<effect>", "<domain>": <matcher>, "sandbox": { "named": "<policy-name>" } } }
```

### Effects

`"allow"` | `"deny"` | `"ask"`

## Capability domains

### Exec — shell commands

```json
{ "exec": { "bin": <pattern>, "args": [ <pattern> ] } }
```

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `bin` | pattern | Binary name matcher |
| `args` | array of patterns | Positional argument matchers (optional) |

### Fs — file operations

```json
{ "fs": { "op": <op-pattern>, "path": <path-filter> } }
```

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `op` | op-pattern | Operation matcher |
| `path` | path-filter | Path matcher (optional) |

### Net — network access

```json
{ "net": { "domain": <pattern> } }
```

### Tool — agent tools

```json
{ "tool": { "name": <pattern> } }
```

## Patterns

```json
{ "literal": "value" }
{ "regex": "pattern" }
{ "glob": "pattern" }
{ "any": null }
{ "or": [ <pattern>, <pattern> ] }
"*"
```

| Form | Description |
|---|---|
| `{"literal": "..."}` | Exact string match |
| `{"regex": "..."}` | Regular expression match |
| `{"glob": "..."}` | Shell glob match |
| `{"any": null}` | Wildcard — matches anything |
| `{"or": [...]}` | Match any of the listed patterns |
| `"*"` | Shorthand wildcard (domains) |

## Op patterns

```json
{ "single": "read" }
{ "or": ["read", "write"] }
"*"
```

Operations: `"read"`, `"write"`, `"create"`, `"delete"`

## Path filters

```json
{ "subpath": { "path": <path-expr> } }
{ "subpath": { "path": <path-expr>, "worktree": true } }
{ "static": "/absolute/path" }
{ "regex": "pattern" }
{ "glob": "pattern" }
```

### Path expressions

```json
{ "env": "PWD" }
{ "static": "/path" }
{ "join": [ <path-expr>, <path-expr> ] }
```

| Form | Description |
|---|---|
| `{"env": "NAME"}` | Resolved from environment variable at compile time |
| `{"static": "..."}` | Literal path string |
| `{"join": [...]}` | Concatenation of path expressions |

## Includes

```json
{ "include": "<policy-name>" }
```

Inlines the referenced policy's rules. Circular includes are rejected at compile time.

## Sandbox references

```json
{ "rule": { "effect": "allow", "exec": { "bin": {"literal": "cargo"} }, "sandbox": { "named": "cargo-env" } } }
```

The `"sandbox"` field on an exec rule references a named policy whose rules define the sandbox's filesystem and network constraints.
